§18-3A-2. Purpose. The purpose of this act is to coordinate and enhance early childhood education and childcare services in West Virginia by requiring the West Virginia Department of Education's Pre-K, Birth to Three, and other early childhood education programs coordinate service delivery.  This initiative aims to improve access, affordability, and quality of early childhood education prograns and childcare for working families while ensuring continuity of care and education from birth to school entry. §18-3A-3. Program Administration. (a) The West Virginia Department of Education and the Department of Health, with input from local school districts, Head Start programs, licensed childcare providers, and parent advocacy groups, shall identify programs providing early childhood education to children in the state, including but not limited, to Pre-K and Birth to Three;(b) Once the programs have been identified, the West Virginia Department of Education and the Department of Health shall coordinate service delivery to ensure that a child, if eligible, will receive all early childhood education benefits available; (c) The coordination of service delivery may include, but not be limited to, determining eligibility for each program, sharing eligibility information between programs with the appropriate consent, or conducting a warm handoff between programs of the parent or guardian and the child. §18-3A-4. Accountability and Oversight.(a) Annual Reporting – The Department of Education shall submit an annual report to the Legislative Oversight Commission on Education Accountability detailing program enrollment, fiscal expenditures, child development outcomes, and areas for improvement beginning July 1, 2026 and July 1 annually thereafter.(b) The Department of Health shall submit an annual report to the Legislative Oversight Commission on Health and Human Resources Accountability detailing program enrollment, fiscal expenditures, child development outcomes, and areas for improvement beginning July 1, 2026 and July 1 annually thereafter. §18-3A-5. Effective Date. This act shall take effect on July 1, 2026. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: